fields.label: Label
fields.name: label
fields.instructions: General name for the post type, usually plural. Default is Posts/Pages

fields.label: Name
fields.name: acfe_dpt_name
fields.instructions: Post type name. Max. 20 characters, cannot contain capital letters or spaces

fields.label: Description
fields.name: description
fields.instructions: A short descriptive summary of the post type

fields.label: Hierarchical
fields.name: hierarchical
fields.instructions: Whether the post type is hierarchical (e.g. page). Allows Parent to be specified. The 'supports' parameter should contain 'page-attributes' to show the parent select box on the editor page.

fields.label: Supports
fields.name: supports
fields.instructions: An alias for calling add_post_type_support() directly. As of 3.5, boolean false can be passed as value instead of an array to prevent default (title and editor) behavior.

fields.label: Taxonomies
fields.name: taxonomies
fields.instructions: An array of registered taxonomies like category or post_tag that will be used with this post type. This can be used in lieu of calling register_taxonomy_for_object_type() directly. Custom taxonomies still need to be registered with register_taxonomy()

fields.label: Public
fields.name: public
fields.instructions: Controls how the type is visible to authors (show_in_nav_menus, show_ui) and readers (exclude_from_search, publicly_queryable)

fields.label: Exclude from search
fields.name: exclude_from_search
fields.instructions: Whether to exclude posts with this post type from front end search results

fields.label: Publicly queryable
fields.name: publicly_queryable
fields.instructions: Whether queries can be performed on the front end as part of parse_request()

fields.label: Can export
fields.name: can_export
fields.instructions: Can this post type be exported

fields.label: Delete with user
fields.name: delete_with_user
fields.instructions:
Whether to delete posts of this type when deleting a user. If true, posts of this type belonging to the user will be moved to trash when then user is deleted.

If false, posts of this type belonging to the user will not be trashed or deleted. If not set (the default), posts are trashed if the post type supports author. Otherwise posts are not trashed or deleted

fields.label: Labels
fields.name: labels
fields.instructions:
An array of labels for this post type. By default, post labels are used for non-hierarchical post types and page labels for hierarchical ones.

Default: if empty, 'name' is set to value of 'label', and 'singular_name' is set to value of 'name'.

fields.label: Menu position
fields.name: menu_position
fields.instructions: The position in the menu order the post type should appear. show_in_menu must be true

fields.label: Menu icon
fields.name: menu_icon
fields.instructions: The url to the icon to be used for this menu or the name of the icon from the iconfont (Dashicons)

fields.label: Show UI
fields.name: show_ui
fields.instructions: Whether to generate a default UI for managing this post type in the admin

fields.label: Show in menu
fields.name: show_in_menu
fields.instructions: Where to show the post type in the admin menu. show_ui must be true

fields.label: Show in menu (text)
fields.name: show_in_menu_text
fields.instructions: If an existing top level page such as 'tools.php' or 'edit.php?post_type=page', the post type will be placed as a sub menu of that

fields.label: Show in nav menus
fields.name: show_in_nav_menus
fields.instructions: Whether post_type is available for selection in navigation menus

fields.label: Show in admin bar
fields.name: show_in_admin_bar
fields.instructions: Where to show the post type in the admin menu. show_ui must be true

fields.label: Capability type
fields.name: capability_type
fields.instructions:
The string to use to build the read, edit, and delete capabilities.
May be passed as an array to allow for alternative plurals when using this argument as a base to construct the capabilities, like this:

story
stories

fields.label: Capabilities
fields.name: capabilities
fields.instructions:
An array of the capabilities for this post type. Specify capabilities like this:

edit_post
read_post
delete_post
edit_posts
etc...

fields.label: Template
fields.name: acfe_dpt_archive_template
fields.instructions: ACF Extended: Which template file to load for the archive query. More informations on Template hierarchy

fields.label: Has archive
fields.name: has_archive
fields.instructions: Enables post type archives.

fields.label: Slug
fields.name: has_archive_slug
fields.instructions: Will use post type name as archive slug by default.

fields.label: Posts per page
fields.name: acfe_dpt_archive_posts_per_page
fields.instructions: ACF Extended: Number of posts to display in the archive page

fields.label: Order by
fields.name: acfe_dpt_archive_orderby
fields.instructions: ACF Extended: Sort retrieved posts by parameter in the archive page. Defaults to 'date (post_date)'.

fields.label: Order
fields.name: acfe_dpt_archive_order
fields.instructions: ACF Extended: Designates the ascending or descending order of the 'orderby' parameter in the archive page. Defaults to 'DESC'.

fields.label: Template
fields.name: acfe_dpt_single_template
fields.instructions: ACF Extended: Which template file to load for the archive query. More informations on Template hierarchy

fields.label: Rewrite
fields.name: rewrite
fields.instructions: Triggers the handling of rewrites for this post type. To prevent rewrites, set to false.

fields.label: Rewrite Arguments
fields.name: rewrite_args_select
fields.instructions: Use additional rewrite arguments

fields.label: Rewrite Arguments
fields.name: rewrite_args
fields.instructions: Additional arguments

sub_fields.label: Slug
sub_fields.name: acfe_dpt_rewrite_slug
sub_fields.instructions: Customize the permalink structure slug. Defaults to the post type name value. Should be translatable.

sub_fields.label: With front
sub_fields.name: acfe_dpt_rewrite_with_front
sub_fields.instructions: Should the permalink structure be prepended with the front base. (example: if your permalink structure is /blog/, then your links will be: false->/news/, true->/blog/news/). Defaults to true.

sub_fields.label: Feeds
sub_fields.name: feeds
sub_fields.instructions: Should a feed permalink structure be built for this post type. Defaults to has_archive value.

sub_fields.label: Pages
sub_fields.name: pages
sub_fields.instructions: Should the permalink structure provide for pagination. Defaults to true.

fields.label: Archive Page
fields.name: acfe_dpt_admin_archive
fields.instructions: Add archive page to the post type administration.

fields.label: Posts per page
fields.name: acfe_dpt_admin_posts_per_page
fields.instructions: ACF Extended: Number of posts to display on the admin list screen

fields.label: Order by
fields.name: acfe_dpt_admin_orderby
fields.instructions: ACF Extended: Sort retrieved posts by parameter in the admin list screen. Defaults to 'date (post_date)'.

fields.label: Order
fields.name: acfe_dpt_admin_order
fields.instructions: ACF Extended: Designates the ascending or descending order of the 'orderby' parameter in the admin list screen. Defaults to 'DESC'.

fields.label: Show in rest
fields.name: show_in_rest
fields.instructions: Whether to expose this post type in the REST API

fields.label: Rest base
fields.name: rest_base
fields.instructions: The base slug that this post type will use when accessed using the REST API

fields.label: Rest controller class
fields.name: rest_controller_class
fields.instructions: An optional custom controller to use instead of WP_REST_Posts_Controller. Must be a subclass of WP_REST_Controller
